            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Remove the <strong>coconut cream</strong> from the sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span>and chop it roughly</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coconut cream</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong> with the <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>roasted garlic paste</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>coconut stock</strong>, the<strong> juice </strong>of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lime</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1693-Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, squeeze the pouch<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span>of <strong>steamed white basmati rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span>(just a little!) and put the pouch in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two packets, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
